caption:
The focus was never on the stage, but on the people and the ideas they stand by.

At TEDx, what emerged were ideas shaped by conviction, tested through real consequences, & shared because they demanded to be said.

@thefurqanstory challenged the idea of waiting to be chosen, showing how proof of work built in public can create opportunity where resumes never reach.
@drsivaranjanionline confronted the cost of silence, demonstrating how truth backed by evidence and persistence can protect lives and force systems to respond. 
@maryam.for.good reframed poverty itself, revealing how lack of exposure quietly limits potential and how guidance and access can alter the direction of an entire life. 
@santosh_speaks questioned progress without humanity, asserting that empathy, listening, and coaching remain the most powerful skills in any future shaped by technology. 
@zonar_x reframed boredom as a signal rather than a flaw, showing how stillness can uncover purpose when noise no longer has answers.
@suneet_sabale connected innovation to freedom, making the case that ideas hold power only when they are owned, protected, & carried with intent.
@theskrathor spoke against the silent erosion of childhood, urging a return to play, connection, and values before screens define growing minds. @drkavya_hepatologist addressed a modern health crisis hiding in plain sight, proving that healing often begins not with complexity, but with discipline, awareness, and basics.

The room emptied & the applause faded. What remained with the audience were ideas still at work.

